Typus
=====

= Doc

To create the first user and copy the stylesheets ...

	rake typus:setup

Default user and password

	username. admin
	password. typus

== Contact

You can contact me at <fesplugas@intraducibles.net>

== Setting your own username and password

You can set your `username` and `password` overwriting the following settings:

  TYPUS['username']
  TYPUS['password]

You can place this settings in a initializer at `config/initializers/typus.rb`

== Configuration file options

If the configuration file is broken you'll see a `typus.yml` text on the admin interface.

=== Lists

  attribute
  attribute::OPTIONS

For example ...

  language::LANGUAGES

where `LANGUAGES` is defined at `config/initializers/typus.rb` as

  LANGUAGES = [["Català", "ca"], ["English", "en"], ["Español", "es"]]

=== Forms

    attribute::string
    attribute::text::10
    attribute::collection <= The attribute is a `belong_to :attribute` relationship.
    status::boolean
    created_at::datetime
    language::selector::LANGUAGES

=== Filters

  status::boolean
  author
  category

=== Order

  attribute::asc
  attribute::desc

=== Search

  attribute1, attribute2

== Integration with Capistrano

  deploy.task :restart, :roles => :app do
  run "cd #{current_path} && rake db:migrate RAILS_ENV=production"
    run "cd #{current_path} && rake typus:setup"
  end

